###

## Problems with Walkthroughs

The two problems in this section have attached video walkthroughs -- try answering the question parts before watching the corresponding walkthrough video. If you run into trouble, hit play on the video and see if you can identify the answers from my walkthrough. Be sure to mark down any questions you have. As a reminder, click below for the detailed versions of the general strategies for inference tasks.

  + [General Strategy for Conducting a Hypothesis Test](www/HTgeneral.pdf)
  + [General Strategy for Computing a Confidence Interval](www/CIgeneral.pdf)

###

**Try It 1:** The result of a poll was that 48% of 331 randomly sampled Americans who decide not to go to college do so because they cannot afford it.

  + Calculate a 90% confidence interval for the proportion of Americans who decide not to go to college because they cannot afford it, and interpret the result in context.

<center>**In Case of Emergency Hit Play** [NEED TO CREATE VIDEO]</center>

Use the code block below to execute any necessary computation.
```{r try-it-1a-code-block, exercise = TRUE}

```

```{r try-it-1a-question-1, echo = FALSE}
question_radio(
  "To answer the question as asked, we should",
  answer("Compute a confidence interval", correct = TRUE),
  answer("Conduct a hypothesis test"),
  answer("Compute a probability"),
  answer("Find a required sample size"),
  allow_retry = TRUE,
  random_answer_order = TRUE
)
```

###

```{r try-it-1a-question-2, echo = FALSE}
question_radio(
  "The point estimate is",
  answer("0.48", correct = TRUE),
  answer("48"),
  answer("331"),
  answer("0.145"),
  answer("159"),
  allow_retry = TRUE,
  random_answer_order = TRUE
)
```

###

```{r try-it-1a-question-3, echo = FALSE}
question_radio(
  "The standard error formula is",
  answer("$\\displaystyle{S_E = \\sqrt{\\frac{p\\left(1-p\\right)}{n}}}$", correct = TRUE),
  answer("$\\displaystyle{S_E = s/\\sqrt{n}}$"),
  answer("$\\displaystyle{S_E = \\sigma/\\sqrt{n}}$"),
  answer("$\\displaystyle{S_E = \\sqrt{\\frac{p_1\\left(1 - p_1\\right)}{n_1} + \\frac{p_2\\left(1 - p_2\\right)}{n_2}}}$"),
  answer("$\\displaystyle{S_E = \\sqrt{\\frac{s_1^2}{n_1} + \\frac{s_2^2}{n_2}}}$"),
  allow_retry = TRUE,
  random_answer_order = TRUE
)
```

